      Returns all possible solutions to a system of equations.
      Syntax: x = solvea({Equations},{Variables})
      Allowed types for x: qubit, cbit, qnum, qnump, cnum, qstr, qstrs, qstrc, qstre, cstr, ctrs, ctrc, cstre, matrix, block, circ, list, dict, set, map.
      Allowed types for Equations: A list or set of strings containing equations written according to this documentation, or one such equation as a string.
      Allowed types for Variables: A list or set of strings containing all of the well-defined variables appearing in the equations, or one such variable as a string.
      Examples:

      x = solvea({"x+1=10"},{"x"}) = solvea("x+1=10","x") = 9 = "x=9" = {"x=9"}
      x = solvea({"x+1=y","y*x=90"},{"x","y"}) = solvea({"x+1=y","y*x=90","y+z=10","z=10-y"},{"x","y"}) = {"x=9, y=10"} = "x=9, y=10"
      x = solvea({"x^2 - 5*x + 6 = 0"},{"x"}) = {"x=2","x=3"} = "x=2, x=3"
      x = solvea({"x^2 + y^2 = 25", "x + y = 7"},{"x","y"}) = {"x=3, y=4", "x=4, y=3"} = "x=3, y=4; x=4, y=3"
      

64. Run circuit
      Run a quantum Circuit with selected backend paramaters and return resulting register
      Circuit = quantum circuit, Backend = Simulator Model, Noise = Noise model, T1 = vector/list of energy relaxation time per qubit in ms, T2 = vector/list of dephasing time per qubit in ms, gate time = matrix of time in takes to apply each gate to each qubit in ms
      Note that t1,t2, & gate_time can be set to lower dimensional types to mean equality, meaning that they can all be numerical types and vector types, with loss of complexity.
      Additionally, T2, T2, & Gate time are optional, dependent on the noise model.
      Backend and Noise are selected via number.
      RNG seeding is available for result reproduction.
      You may include shots to run the simulation a number of times, this will return the most common resulting register.
      If you wish to recieve a histogram instead, use 'Run circuit with histogram' or 'runh()' instead.
      Syntax: 
      x = run(Circuit)  | Default backend / backend №0
      or
      x = run(Circuit, Backend)
      or 
      x = run(Circuit, Backend, Noise)
      or
      x = run(Circuit, Backend, Noise, T1, T2, Gate_time)
      or
      x = run(Shots, Circuit)  | Default backend / backend №0
      or
      x = run(Shots, Circuit, Backend)
      or 
